html: 9.22.22  6:12 am   "Pave the way all the way from yesterday to another day." I love this line. You don't say "tomorrow," but "another day," as if there's no great expectation for the future. Nothing HAS to change from yesterday. The question is whether the road has been paved for change to take place eventually. Or no change whatsoever as you keep going down a more determined, safer road. It inspires resilience and perseverance even if you don't end up starting a revolution. Feeling proud of just "going through the motions" and working hard for yourself. And knowing you're not the only road-paver in this life, as lives touch each other to create love.
